WEBVTT

00:00:46.500 --> 00:00:48.540
Supa told me that Dr. Nong just arrived in Phu Chaloem.

00:00:48.790 --> 00:00:49.900
He’s in the office, packing up.

00:00:52.310 --> 00:00:53.220
I screwed up.

00:00:54.570 --> 00:00:56.340
I should’ve had the guts to tell them from the start.

00:00:58.060 --> 00:00:59.500
Beating yourself up won’t help now.

00:00:59.890 --> 00:01:01.060
Go bring the doc back.

00:01:01.770 --> 00:01:02.740
He’s not coming back.

00:01:04.260 --> 00:01:05.540
You’re giving up just like that?

00:01:05.960 --> 00:01:08.060
If you look into his eyes, then you’d know.

00:01:14.820 --> 00:01:19.180
Dr. Nong might’ve been angry at that moment, but he wasn’t angry at you.

00:01:20.000 --> 00:01:21.780
He’s probably mad at whoever cut the deal with Phasakorn

00:01:22.310 --> 00:01:24.700
Which you still haven’t owned up to,
have you?

00:01:25.510 --> 00:01:26.820
You already knew, didn’t you?

00:01:28.420 --> 00:01:31.260
All I knew was that my father
wanted to make you minister.

00:01:32.300 --> 00:01:36.060
But I only found out about
dropping the policy right in that meeting.

00:01:36.860 --> 00:01:38.340
Can you calm down for a second?

00:01:40.290 --> 00:01:41.740
And you still want me to calm down?

00:01:44.620 --> 00:01:48.860
I think once he cools off,
he might hear you out.

00:01:49.370 --> 00:01:51.100
Think he’ll cool off in time to be sworn in?

00:01:53.020 --> 00:01:56.100
He won’t even look me in the eye right now,

00:01:56.860 --> 00:01:57.900
there’s no chance of talking.

00:02:05.030 --> 00:02:07.020
Or use the same tactic to convince him?

00:02:07.460 --> 00:02:10.600
Talk ideals, play to his ego like,

00:02:10.710 --> 00:02:13.340
“If it’s not you, Doc,
no one can pull this off.”

00:02:17.700 --> 00:02:18.580
Honestly,

00:02:21.350 --> 00:02:24.180
you two could stop
being politicians for a minute.

00:02:30.250 --> 00:02:34.420
I don’t know how messy this is,

00:02:36.540 --> 00:02:38.260
but if someone knows they were wrong,

00:02:39.940 --> 00:02:41.140
they should apologize.

00:02:44.020 --> 00:02:45.100
That’s it.

00:02:48.940 --> 00:02:52.100
No prep, no plan.

00:02:54.600 --> 00:02:56.660
Just talk like you mean it.

00:03:03.980 --> 00:03:06.140
I think Jump’s right.

00:03:10.200 --> 00:03:12.740
you go bring the doc back.

00:03:12.860 --> 00:03:14.940
I’ll buy us some time on this end.

00:04:14.170 --> 00:04:17.180
You think running the Interior Ministry
means you can do whatever you want?

00:04:17.710 --> 00:04:19.540
If it were that easy,

00:04:20.250 --> 00:04:23.060
why would I need to grovel to that bastard?

00:04:24.100 --> 00:04:26.260
I don’t see what the big deal is.

00:04:26.870 --> 00:04:28.940
And Uncle Wut’s already fine with the deal.

00:04:30.120 --> 00:04:33.220
You don’t know him,
he’s tricky as hell.

00:04:34.020 --> 00:04:35.140
I can handle it.

00:04:35.400 --> 00:04:36.780
You can handle his son, that’s all.

00:04:38.290 --> 00:04:40.180
From now on, you don’t say a damn word.

00:04:40.610 --> 00:04:41.900
I’ll handle it myself.

00:04:42.520 --> 00:04:45.400
- Chon, get Wut on the line.
- Don’t.

00:04:47.020 --> 00:04:48.460
Calling him won’t change a thing, Dad.

00:04:49.510 --> 00:04:50.820
I figured after your ordination,

00:04:50.900 --> 00:04:53.060
you’d have absorbed enough Dhamma
to keep your cool.

00:04:56.460 --> 00:04:57.620
You’re fired.

00:04:58.270 --> 00:05:00.260
Chon, you’re the party leader.

00:05:01.610 --> 00:05:03.220
Looks like we’re not going
to see eye to eye.

00:05:03.820 --> 00:05:04.860
Here’s the deal.

00:05:05.860 --> 00:05:08.420
I’ve got key evidence
Nititham still doesn’t have.

00:05:09.060 --> 00:05:11.660
If it comes out, we all go down,

00:05:12.100 --> 00:05:13.060
not just you.

00:05:13.870 --> 00:05:15.540
But Chon and I
are going to be screwed, too.

00:05:17.260 --> 00:05:19.300
So you’ve got two options:

00:05:19.670 --> 00:05:24.580
One: step back and serve your sentence
with VIP treatment.

00:05:25.220 --> 00:05:28.820
Or two,
which I wouldn’t recommend,

00:05:30.450 --> 00:05:34.100
go to prison like everyone else
and be left with nothing.

00:05:36.780 --> 00:05:38.060
You got the guts?

00:05:44.220 --> 00:05:45.540
What do you think?

00:05:52.460 --> 00:05:53.700
With respect, I’ll take my leave.

00:06:01.700 --> 00:06:02.740
There we go

00:06:08.710 --> 00:06:09.500
good,

00:06:10.140 --> 00:06:12.900
good, good. Very good.

00:06:16.020 --> 00:06:18.900
Try again. You can stand… there,

00:06:20.650 --> 00:06:23.660
you’re up! you’re up!

00:06:28.080 --> 00:06:28.780
Dad

00:06:29.410 --> 00:06:30.580
Ow, my back.

00:06:32.900 --> 00:06:34.020
You okay, Dad?

00:06:35.070 --> 00:06:37.300
Easy, easy. I’m fine.

00:06:38.660 --> 00:06:39.980
Go check on your sister.

00:06:42.410 --> 00:06:45.380
Ning, Are you okay?

00:06:55.180 --> 00:07:00.780
Kid, look your brother’s here.

00:07:01.170 --> 00:07:04.780
He hasn’t said a word since
he got back.

00:07:05.480 --> 00:07:07.820
No idea what’s weighing on him.

00:07:09.770 --> 00:07:13.100
Go try talking to him.

00:07:14.520 --> 00:07:15.860
Go try talking to him.

00:07:22.110 --> 00:07:23.380
Hey…

00:07:27.450 --> 00:07:28.500
I lost.

00:07:33.850 --> 00:07:36.580
I helped them all the way
to winning the election,

00:07:41.220 --> 00:07:43.660
I was supposed to be made minister.

00:07:47.580 --> 00:07:52.220
But they’d been stringing me
along the whole time.

00:08:03.860 --> 00:08:05.180
I’m sorry.

00:08:07.950 --> 00:08:09.900
I can’t keep my promise.

00:08:29.660 --> 00:08:30.860
Nong,

00:08:33.460 --> 00:08:35.500
if it’s too much, just come home.

00:08:35.900 --> 00:08:37.900
Take care of the family.

00:08:38.910 --> 00:08:42.340
T Don’t worry about the rest,
it’s not worth it, son.

00:08:51.460 --> 00:08:52.660
What are you doing here?

00:08:56.020 --> 00:08:56.900
Just go.

00:09:01.500 --> 00:09:02.300
Doc,

00:09:03.090 --> 00:09:05.500
let me say one thing for the last time.

00:09:06.890 --> 00:09:08.820
Then I won’t bother you again.

00:09:09.800 --> 00:09:10.620
Please?

00:09:33.300 --> 00:09:34.940
I want to apologize. I lied.

00:09:37.080 --> 00:09:38.740
When they scrapped your policy,

00:09:39.380 --> 00:09:40.780
I was in that room too.

00:09:47.200 --> 00:09:50.700
And I owe an apology to Uncle
and to Dr. Ning

00:09:51.410 --> 00:09:54.220
for failing to deliver
the policy she entrusted to me.

00:09:56.600 --> 00:09:59.340
I tried to push back,
but I couldn’t win.

00:10:03.460 --> 00:10:05.540
What’s the point of telling me now?

00:10:07.540 --> 00:10:08.540
I’m sorry.

00:10:11.120 --> 00:10:13.780
I had the chance to tell you,
but I didn’t.

00:10:15.250 --> 00:10:16.540
I never meant to hide it.

00:10:18.800 --> 00:10:21.820
I was just afraid that if you knew,

00:10:24.060 --> 00:10:25.380
we’d end up like this.

00:10:35.850 --> 00:10:37.540
Instead of sitting here,

00:10:40.430 --> 00:10:41.900
go finish the job.

00:10:44.370 --> 00:10:45.900
Take that as a personal ask from me.

00:10:47.190 --> 00:10:48.820
I can’t without you.

00:10:52.180 --> 00:10:54.980
All I’m good at is talking people
into doing things.

00:10:55.940 --> 00:10:59.180
We got this far because of you.

00:11:01.610 --> 00:11:02.700
Thank you,

00:11:05.320 --> 00:11:07.060
and I’m sorry you trusted me.

00:11:11.630 --> 00:11:13.700
I already signed a resignation letter
and left it with Jes.

00:11:15.020 --> 00:11:17.340
It takes effect the moment
my father approves it.

00:11:20.170 --> 00:11:21.420
I’m just saying,

00:11:22.960 --> 00:11:25.780
you can’t count on me
for anything anymore.

00:11:27.620 --> 00:11:29.020
If you quit, I quit.

00:11:42.900 --> 00:11:43.900
I’ll get going now.

00:12:13.685 --> 00:12:14.740
What is it… Ning?

00:12:16.850 --> 00:12:19.260
Slowly. I’m listening.

00:12:33.980 --> 00:12:35.700
F… fight…

00:12:51.492 --> 00:12:52.300
Mm.

00:12:54.850 --> 00:12:55.700
Fight.

00:13:14.860 --> 00:13:15.860
All right, let’s do this.

00:13:18.340 --> 00:13:19.220
I’m ready.

00:13:20.942 --> 00:13:22.020
The Minister is ready.

00:13:25.764 --> 00:13:28.660
And remember, left foot first,

00:13:29.520 --> 00:13:31.020
Mr.Vee instructed me to remind you.

00:13:36.985 --> 00:13:38.900
Minister! Sir!

00:13:39.442 --> 00:13:41.300
Good morning.

00:13:42.780 --> 00:13:44.100
Okay, everyone,

00:13:45.180 --> 00:13:46.260
easy, please.

00:13:46.980 --> 00:13:49.180
First off, don’t call me ‘Minister’

00:13:49.540 --> 00:13:51.260
Just call me Dr. Nong.

00:13:51.450 --> 00:13:57.780
Because with the title or without,
I’m still the same old Dr. Nong.

00:14:02.500 --> 00:14:05.900
Is cutting down doctors’
working hours your first task in the office?

00:14:08.540 --> 00:14:09.460
Yes,

00:14:10.480 --> 00:14:13.220
I’ll go straight into it. But first,

00:14:13.550 --> 00:14:17.460
we’ll need to set up a committee
and a team to study feasibility.

00:14:17.560 --> 00:14:22.420
There’s talk you’re just a puppet minister
with no real power.

00:14:22.590 --> 00:14:25.620
Can you actually deliver
your own policies?

00:14:26.180 --> 00:14:28.620
I’m not working alone,

00:14:29.380 --> 00:14:30.860
and we’re working as a team.

00:14:32.060 --> 00:14:38.100
I don’t have the kind of power
where I can snap my fingers and it’s done.

00:14:38.470 --> 00:14:41.780
Wiwat Siam has a lot on the policy slate,

00:14:42.220 --> 00:14:47.100
so I can’t say yet what comes first.

00:14:47.440 --> 00:14:52.740
But whatever I take on,
I’ll give it everything.

00:14:54.720 --> 00:14:57.740
Minister, how do you feel
on your first day?

00:15:00.628 --> 00:15:02.460
Good.

00:15:02.770 --> 00:15:08.340
I’m glad to be meeting the team
we’ll be working with on my day one...

00:15:09.505 --> 00:15:11.780
I already told you,

00:15:12.240 --> 00:15:15.180
this didn’t need to go
all the way up to the Minister.

00:15:16.940 --> 00:15:18.820
I wanted to learn the ropes myself.

00:15:20.020 --> 00:15:21.780
I don’t see any problem.

00:15:23.210 --> 00:15:25.140
I’ve reviewed the basics.

00:15:25.690 --> 00:15:30.228
We’ll call it the Tele-Doctor Program
so it doesn’t overlap with Telemed.

00:15:30.400 --> 00:15:31.980
And Phasakorn has no objections.

00:15:32.980 --> 00:15:33.820
All right.

00:15:35.900 --> 00:15:36.780
Ying,

00:15:38.420 --> 00:15:41.420
but technically, something like this
has to go through a tender, right?

00:15:43.540 --> 00:15:44.460
It does,

00:15:45.140 --> 00:15:48.220
I but Med Tech will win the bid.

00:15:48.570 --> 00:15:50.540
- If you’re thinking that…
- It’s fine.

00:15:51.680 --> 00:15:53.060
I know exactly where I stand.

00:15:57.060 --> 00:16:01.060
Nationwide,
the Tele-Doctor has twelve hubs.

00:16:03.170 --> 00:16:05.500
Puea Khwam Wang has already taken six.

00:16:07.020 --> 00:16:08.860
Doesn’t get clearer than that.

00:16:09.120 --> 00:16:13.220
It’s tele-doctors.
You can work from anywhere anyway.

00:16:17.171 --> 00:16:19.620
Or should we shift one hub
to Phu Chaloem?

00:16:20.740 --> 00:16:22.180
I think that’s workable.

00:16:23.450 --> 00:16:24.700
I’ll definitely move them,

00:16:25.640 --> 00:16:27.500
but let me study the data a bit more.

00:16:27.830 --> 00:16:30.700
This is only phase one, though.

00:16:30.942 --> 00:16:32.140
- I think, Doctor
- Don’t worry.

00:16:32.840 --> 00:16:33.980
I’ll sign off on your part.

00:16:36.620 --> 00:16:38.820
And tell Passakorn,

00:16:39.770 --> 00:16:41.980
I won’t touch his quota.

00:16:42.860 --> 00:16:44.460
But as for the other six,

00:16:45.120 --> 00:16:46.780
I’m going to tweak the specs a little

00:16:47.460 --> 00:16:49.260
for the public good.

00:16:51.020 --> 00:16:54.620
I’m sure he won’t be petty about it.

00:17:03.100 --> 00:17:06.500
You walk in and go straight for a drink, huh?

00:17:07.400 --> 00:17:08.300
Come on,

00:17:09.360 --> 00:17:10.580
it’s the adjustment period.

00:17:11.350 --> 00:17:13.300
I need a beer to decompress.

00:17:14.114 --> 00:17:15.420
The one who’s really stressed

00:17:16.760 --> 00:17:18.180
already called to complain about you.

00:17:19.380 --> 00:17:20.260
For real?

00:17:23.460 --> 00:17:25.980
I do want to stay on Ying’s good side,

00:17:26.780 --> 00:17:29.940
but Dr. Chalong is a pain in the ass.

00:17:31.450 --> 00:17:34.460
Heard it was you giving him the pain.

00:17:35.660 --> 00:17:36.980
How could I not?

00:17:37.770 --> 00:17:39.660
They’ve left me
with only six sites to run.

00:17:40.620 --> 00:17:42.140
It’s not like I can do much.

00:17:44.460 --> 00:17:45.300
Oh yeah?

00:17:46.740 --> 00:17:47.540
Yeah.

00:17:49.460 --> 00:17:51.420
Basically, you line them up by population

00:17:51.620 --> 00:17:54.100
and put the hub
where they’ll help the most.

00:17:54.620 --> 00:17:56.980
Meds and equipment go where

00:17:57.420 --> 00:18:00.980
the local illness stats say they’re needed.

00:18:01.980 --> 00:18:05.620
And I’m looping
in community health workers.

00:18:05.980 --> 00:18:06.860
That’s it.

00:18:07.171 --> 00:18:08.180
That’s it, huh.

00:18:09.740 --> 00:18:11.300
Not exactly ‘not much.’

00:18:15.130 --> 00:18:19.500
Don’t forget, you’re a minister.

00:18:19.991 --> 00:18:21.740
This isn’t the only thing on your plate.

00:18:23.610 --> 00:18:26.220
It’s you who shouldn’t forget
who you’re talking to.

00:18:27.064 --> 00:18:28.900
This is the powerhouse, Dr. Nong.

00:18:30.180 --> 00:18:31.420
Don’t underestimate me.

00:18:32.900 --> 00:18:34.580
You do look like you’re enjoying the job.

00:18:36.410 --> 00:18:37.460
Not fun at all.

00:18:38.850 --> 00:18:39.980
But I’ve got a target now.

00:18:40.700 --> 00:18:42.420
If we can’t change everything,

00:18:43.920 --> 00:18:45.300
we change what we can.

00:18:51.314 --> 00:18:52.780
Young Siam gets
the green light once again.

00:18:54.020 --> 00:18:55.820
This time we hit the campuses,

00:18:57.860 --> 00:19:02.340
so we’ll get to sail the ship
just as you wanted.

00:19:05.760 --> 00:19:07.060
As I wanted.

00:19:09.220 --> 00:19:10.420
And you?

00:19:13.060 --> 00:19:14.020
Sounds good to me.

00:19:15.700 --> 00:19:16.660
But you,

00:19:18.100 --> 00:19:22.140
will you have time
to take me out for dessert?

00:19:26.524 --> 00:19:30.500
You’ll have to check with my secretary.

00:19:32.300 --> 00:19:37.660
I hear your secretary’s supposed
to brief me on your schedule.

00:19:39.100 --> 00:19:44.820
Then you already know,
I’m always free for you.

00:19:46.770 --> 00:19:49.660
if I call,

00:19:51.020 --> 00:19:52.780
free or not,

00:19:53.330 --> 00:19:56.020
you make yourself free.

00:19:56.950 --> 00:19:58.940
You outrank the minister, huh.

00:19:59.300 --> 00:20:00.100
Of course.

00:20:00.500 --> 00:20:03.580
All right then. You’ve got a deal, MP.

00:20:04.540 --> 00:20:05.420
Yes,

00:20:06.060 --> 00:20:07.740
Minister.

00:20:10.840 --> 00:20:15.500
Looks like this might be
the best deal of my political life.

00:20:17.220 --> 00:20:18.540
You talk like you’ve been one for ages.

00:20:19.620 --> 00:20:20.940
Given the way things look,

00:20:21.420 --> 00:20:24.580
just rotten,
cutthroat deals everywhere,

00:20:25.310 --> 00:20:27.180
in a year, ten, twenty…

00:20:28.460 --> 00:20:30.780
There won’t be a better deal than this.

00:20:32.228 --> 00:20:35.260
If there isn’t, make one.

00:20:36.830 --> 00:20:39.700
Give it time,
you’ll have the chops to take them on.

00:20:41.670 --> 00:20:42.700
Bring it on.

00:20:43.810 --> 00:20:45.380
Watch me.

00:20:46.500 --> 00:20:50.380
Titles fade, legends last forever.

00:20:53.057 --> 00:20:54.220
Can’t argue with that.

00:21:03.060 --> 00:21:05.340
(1 Year Later)

00:21:07.610 --> 00:21:09.300
Since it’s December,

00:21:09.620 --> 00:21:14.300
it’s been almost a year
since Khunawut’s cabinet took office.

00:21:14.420 --> 00:21:16.940
Over the past year,
there’s been little to show,

00:21:17.420 --> 00:21:20.740
just budget cuts to prop up
the Eyes Wide Open Fund,

00:21:20.970 --> 00:21:23.780
which ultimately couldn’t pay
every farming household.

00:21:24.440 --> 00:21:27.380
What was 30,000 baht
is now cut down to 10,000.

00:21:28.340 --> 00:21:31.180
Before we move on to
the no-confidence motion,

00:21:31.320 --> 00:21:33.260
here’s the latest news:

00:21:33.480 --> 00:21:36.740
former monk and former prime minister Phanu

00:21:37.020 --> 00:21:39.980
has disrobed and been arrested
on charges of corruption,

00:21:40.200 --> 00:21:41.940
abuse of office to benefit
himself and his allies,

00:21:42.090 --> 00:21:43.380
and soliciting bribes.

00:21:43.580 --> 00:21:47.900
He will be remanded immediately
without bail.

00:21:50.134 --> 00:21:53.180
Try this angle.
They spook at bad press.

00:21:55.921 --> 00:21:56.860
Right,

00:21:58.060 --> 00:21:59.620
because they’ve got skeletons.

00:22:01.220 --> 00:22:02.140
Okay.

00:22:07.500 --> 00:22:08.580
The meeting ran long.

00:22:10.460 --> 00:22:11.940
It’s about telemedicine.

00:22:13.020 --> 00:22:16.300
Dr. Chalong told me that
Dr. Phat won’t budge.

00:22:17.210 --> 00:22:19.660
He insists the hub
goes to his district first.

00:22:21.180 --> 00:22:22.180
Makes zero sense.

00:22:26.742 --> 00:22:27.780
Hold on,

00:22:28.620 --> 00:22:31.660
let me reply to one more chat,
it’s an important one.

00:22:32.650 --> 00:22:33.740
One sec.

00:22:34.881 --> 00:22:36.340
Water’s fine on that end.

00:22:37.210 --> 00:22:39.860
Ministry rules say no alcohol on duty.

00:22:44.171 --> 00:22:46.100
Who’s on duty? Not me.

00:22:47.380 --> 00:22:50.500
And we’re off the clock,

00:22:52.050 --> 00:22:52.940
go ahead.

00:23:11.410 --> 00:23:12.780
A toast, Vee.

00:23:16.114 --> 00:23:17.820
What’s the occasion?

00:23:19.400 --> 00:23:23.580
That we haven’t had dinner out,
just the two of us…in,

00:23:25.057 --> 00:23:27.900
wow, over a month.

00:23:29.500 --> 00:23:31.820
Guess that makes it a special occasion.

00:23:33.340 --> 00:23:35.220
‘Special occasion,’ huh.

00:23:36.940 --> 00:23:38.900
Guilty as charged.

00:23:39.620 --> 00:23:40.940
I’m really sorry.

00:23:41.660 --> 00:23:44.100
Please,

00:23:45.360 --> 00:23:48.180
I’ve been holding this glass so long,
I’m getting a cramp.

00:24:23.457 --> 00:24:24.460
What are you looking at?

00:24:26.690 --> 00:24:27.860
Did I spill something on myself?

00:24:28.860 --> 00:24:29.860
No.

00:24:31.970 --> 00:24:34.500
I was thinking about
the first time we came here.

00:24:37.457 --> 00:24:38.460
I remember.

00:24:40.230 --> 00:24:43.140
First rule, when the food’s served,

00:24:43.580 --> 00:24:46.580
you gently unfold the napkin

00:24:47.770 --> 00:24:49.340
and place it on your lap, like this.

00:24:50.971 --> 00:24:52.460
Just a blink and a year went by.

00:24:53.180 --> 00:24:55.020
You look a lot more… ministerial now.

00:24:56.500 --> 00:24:58.260
Look at me, full of grease.

00:24:59.330 --> 00:25:00.220
Mm.

00:25:02.900 --> 00:25:04.300
I mean grace.

00:25:05.160 --> 00:25:06.540
You could correct me.

00:25:09.010 --> 00:25:11.420
Cheap jokes, huh.

00:25:11.901 --> 00:25:13.580
Who else am I supposed to joke with?

00:25:14.250 --> 00:25:15.580
Ying?

00:25:16.610 --> 00:25:18.260
Or should it be Dr. Chalong?

00:25:19.660 --> 00:25:20.940
It’s gotta be you.

00:25:26.540 --> 00:25:27.540
Truth is,

00:25:29.890 --> 00:25:31.940
I’ve been waiting for tonight all week.

00:25:33.390 --> 00:25:34.780
Waiting just to crack jokes?

00:25:38.580 --> 00:25:40.220
Actually…

00:25:44.420 --> 00:25:46.180
there’s something I wanted to tell you.

00:25:49.230 --> 00:25:50.300
What about?

00:25:53.935 --> 00:25:59.740
We’ve been living together
for a year now.

00:26:02.485 --> 00:26:03.860
I feel…

00:26:04.920 --> 00:26:07.460
something’s changed...

00:26:11.080 --> 00:26:12.140
in me.

00:26:15.700 --> 00:26:16.660
What?

00:26:38.180 --> 00:26:39.140
Yes, Father…

00:26:40.380 --> 00:26:41.340
It’s all set.

00:26:42.420 --> 00:26:44.420
I’ve had the paperwork taken care of.

00:26:51.342 --> 00:26:53.420
Tell Dr. Chalong to knock it off.

00:26:53.900 --> 00:26:54.700
That’ll be all.

00:27:01.230 --> 00:27:03.820
Take it down a notch, Minister,

00:27:04.220 --> 00:27:05.900
they can hear you from out there.

00:27:06.980 --> 00:27:07.900
You’re exaggerating.

00:27:11.360 --> 00:27:13.060
Still hitting hard as ever, huh?

00:27:14.828 --> 00:27:15.780
Yeah.

00:27:16.980 --> 00:27:18.820
I’m still responsible
for people’s lives, aren’t I?

00:27:22.400 --> 00:27:25.300
So, what can I help you with?

00:27:29.001 --> 00:27:30.380
Your same old problem.

00:27:31.971 --> 00:27:32.820
Which one?

00:27:33.960 --> 00:27:37.340
I’ve got a hundred old headaches
and a thousand new ones.

00:27:38.750 --> 00:27:40.180
Boss Jom.

00:27:40.730 --> 00:27:45.180
He’s wrecking my fertilizer
and pesticide reduction program.

00:27:46.692 --> 00:27:48.300
His dad runs Interior,

00:27:48.820 --> 00:27:52.980
so all the subdistrict
and village chiefs are on their side.

00:27:53.714 --> 00:27:57.020
I came to ask how we take them on.

00:27:59.695 --> 00:28:01.660
Now’s not the time to go head-to-head.

00:28:04.340 --> 00:28:06.100
You’ll just make the job harder.

00:28:09.550 --> 00:28:11.100
Try cutting a deal first.

00:28:12.220 --> 00:28:13.420
We can probably negotiate with him.

00:28:14.220 --> 00:28:16.340
You want me to deal
with that old bastard Jom?

00:28:17.050 --> 00:28:20.140
The guy you cursed out
in front of the whole province?

00:28:23.385 --> 00:28:24.780
Listen to me, Nath.

00:28:26.742 --> 00:28:31.180
Like it or not,
these are the rules right now.

00:28:32.457 --> 00:28:34.340
If we can’t change the rules yet,

00:28:35.020 --> 00:28:36.700
we play by them. Right?

00:28:38.978 --> 00:28:42.140
You’ve changed.

00:28:43.171 --> 00:28:44.380
I haven’t.

00:28:45.470 --> 00:28:48.420
I’m doing whatever it takes
to get the work done.

00:28:49.428 --> 00:28:51.660
You just don’t like it this way, that’s all.

00:28:55.142 --> 00:28:57.180
- Seriously?
- Yeah.

00:28:58.692 --> 00:29:02.740
I know what I’m doing,
and I know what I’ll get out of it.

00:29:02.914 --> 00:29:05.820
And you don’t think
about what you’re losing?

00:29:06.848 --> 00:29:08.180
Back then or now.

00:29:08.770 --> 00:29:10.580
I’ve always been willing
to trade whatever it takes.

00:29:11.685 --> 00:29:14.620
You’ve gone too far.

00:29:15.171 --> 00:29:16.500
Or are you stopping here?

00:29:21.742 --> 00:29:23.980
That’s it for today.

00:29:24.850 --> 00:29:25.940
We’ll talk later.

00:29:27.124 --> 00:29:29.340
Go on, I’ve got a lot of work to do.

00:29:37.534 --> 00:29:41.620
I don’t think
I’ve got anything left to say to you.

00:30:20.285 --> 00:30:23.940
I still haven’t properly thanked you
for always having my back.

00:30:25.200 --> 00:30:26.620
Happy birthday, son.

00:30:28.900 --> 00:30:29.940
Go on,

00:30:31.580 --> 00:30:32.940
open it.

00:30:42.257 --> 00:30:43.380
Thank you, Dad.

00:30:48.334 --> 00:30:51.980
The Tele-Doctor program’s been
getting good feedback.

00:30:52.650 --> 00:30:54.380
Almost a year passed,

00:30:54.780 --> 00:30:57.980
and Trirat is gearing up
for the no-confidence motion.

00:30:58.464 --> 00:31:02.940
Frankly, Dr. Nong’s project is about
the only thing that really holds up.

00:31:04.550 --> 00:31:06.820
Only if he could work with fewer hurdles.

00:31:07.340 --> 00:31:08.500
What do you think?

00:31:10.000 --> 00:31:11.860
People would benefit more.

00:31:13.260 --> 00:31:15.660
But Sun won’t make it easy for him.

00:31:15.967 --> 00:31:20.300
Exactly. That’s why I called you in.

00:31:22.971 --> 00:31:24.340
When we formed the government,

00:31:24.650 --> 00:31:28.660
I handed him everything.
Now he’s acting up,

00:31:29.360 --> 00:31:32.660
we need to rein him in.

00:31:33.110 --> 00:31:36.100
There isn’t much we can do,
unless we reshuffle the cabinet.

00:31:36.260 --> 00:31:37.460
A reshuffle won’t fix it.

00:31:37.980 --> 00:31:40.940
A man who could have
his own father thrown in jail

00:31:41.300 --> 00:31:43.540
isn’t giving up power quietly.

00:31:46.342 --> 00:31:48.500
But we can clip his wings.

00:31:49.740 --> 00:31:55.540
If Tele-Doctor Phase 2 switches vendors
from Med Tech to O.P.M., from our side.

00:31:56.100 --> 00:31:59.540
If we can pull that off,
Nong’s job will get a lot easier.

00:32:02.240 --> 00:32:05.020
And tell Dr. Nong to be proactive
about taking credit.

00:32:05.290 --> 00:32:07.420
If the work’s good, then people
should know who’s behind it.

00:32:07.750 --> 00:32:11.340
The more Sun plants
those hubs on his own turf,

00:32:11.770 --> 00:32:16.620
the more openings Nong
has to go in and build support.

00:32:17.020 --> 00:32:20.300
Depends on how much Sun lets us.

00:32:23.657 --> 00:32:25.500
That’s on you now.

00:32:40.685 --> 00:32:42.020
Don’t let anything fall through the cracks.

00:32:42.257 --> 00:32:44.300
Why is it that he more we work,
the more there is to do?

00:32:44.628 --> 00:32:45.740
Ask the boss.

00:32:50.460 --> 00:32:51.540
Same old story.

00:32:52.420 --> 00:32:56.380
And Med Tech
just sent their Phase 2 plan.

00:32:57.260 --> 00:32:58.540
This time it’s worse than before,

00:32:59.650 --> 00:33:01.700
so we’ve got more prep to do.

00:33:01.992 --> 00:33:05.340
Even when you tell it,
you never tell the whole story, do you?

00:33:06.130 --> 00:33:06.980
Jump,

00:33:08.914 --> 00:33:09.820
zip it.

00:33:12.857 --> 00:33:13.940
It’s nothing.

00:33:15.010 --> 00:33:17.420
When the workload piles up,

00:33:17.600 --> 00:33:20.660
the load is too heavy
for the people in the ministry.

00:33:22.171 --> 00:33:26.380
They can’t move at our pace,
so I’m doing it myself.

00:33:28.092 --> 00:33:32.100
They ‘accidentally’
broke the printer and the PCs,

00:33:32.860 --> 00:33:36.220
every dataset took weeks.

00:33:37.780 --> 00:33:40.740
Nobody calls that workload, boss.

00:33:43.250 --> 00:33:44.940
Mouth shut, back to work.

00:33:45.064 --> 00:33:46.220
Go easy.

00:33:47.220 --> 00:33:48.700
You’re making enemies.

00:33:49.220 --> 00:33:52.460
So are you reading everything
they shove at you to sign closely?

00:33:53.580 --> 00:33:56.420
Plenty of ministers have been
set up and knocked over, mind you.

00:33:57.140 --> 00:33:59.060
No matter how big we are,

00:33:59.660 --> 00:34:03.140
we’re political appointees.
We come and go.

00:34:03.960 --> 00:34:06.660
The civil service stays.

00:34:08.140 --> 00:34:11.420
If they’re unhappy, nothing moves.

00:34:12.314 --> 00:34:13.220
Got it, Vee.

00:34:13.340 --> 00:34:16.660
I’m here! Time for a break.

00:34:17.160 --> 00:34:22.100
I heard your dad gave you a present.

00:34:23.700 --> 00:34:26.820
Where is it? Let me see.
Is it worth millions?

00:34:28.900 --> 00:34:30.820
No. Come on.

00:34:33.220 --> 00:34:37.060
Still, I bet Big Boss
wants something in return.

00:34:37.520 --> 00:34:41.380
People like that don’t give freebies.

00:34:49.971 --> 00:34:53.980
Kidding! Don’t tense up.

00:34:56.710 --> 00:34:57.940
You’re right, though.

00:34:59.100 --> 00:35:03.460
He wants the Tele-Doctor supplier
switched to a company on our side.

00:35:04.120 --> 00:35:05.140
Fine by me.

00:35:06.030 --> 00:35:08.700
Doubt there’s any outfit worse
than Med Tech.

00:35:09.860 --> 00:35:12.020
They’re number one at that.

00:35:12.690 --> 00:35:14.900
But we need two things. One:

00:35:16.260 --> 00:35:19.220
you need to get out front
and claim your wins,

00:35:19.820 --> 00:35:21.620
especially on Sun’s turf.

00:35:22.770 --> 00:35:24.540
Sure. That’s easy.

00:35:25.860 --> 00:35:29.020
Two: I have to go
cut a deal with Sun.

00:35:35.035 --> 00:35:35.900
Yeah?

00:35:36.390 --> 00:35:42.220
And what are you putting on the table?

00:35:44.110 --> 00:35:45.180
Nothing yet.

00:35:46.180 --> 00:35:47.580
I’ll talk first.

00:35:49.220 --> 00:35:50.700
If it doesn’t fly, we’ll rethink.

00:35:59.260 --> 00:36:00.660
Are you okay with that?

00:36:08.372 --> 00:36:09.260
It’s fine.

00:36:11.090 --> 00:36:15.457
We trust each other, don’t we?

00:36:33.314 --> 00:36:34.580
Dr. Nong, Mr. Vee.

00:36:35.260 --> 00:36:38.620
Hello, I’m the admin of your ship page.

00:36:38.934 --> 00:36:41.140
Which page? Or are you on Instagram?

00:36:41.492 --> 00:36:42.940
Withu–Thanit.

00:36:44.340 --> 00:36:46.340
Mr. Vee, you’re Croissant, right?

00:36:48.171 --> 00:36:49.340
Oh-ho,

00:36:50.220 --> 00:36:51.340
so you’ve got a burner account?

00:36:54.000 --> 00:36:55.060
Come on, spill.

00:36:55.360 --> 00:36:56.500
What do you guys talk about?

00:36:58.885 --> 00:36:59.780
Doctor.

00:37:02.671 --> 00:37:07.940
Okay, I won’t tell anyone.
I’ll get going. Bye!

00:37:11.600 --> 00:37:12.500
Well,

00:37:13.820 --> 00:37:14.940
Croissant…

00:37:15.942 --> 00:37:18.260
Where are you running off to,
Mr. Croissant?

00:37:20.685 --> 00:37:24.260
Keep it up, and I’ll stop calling you Vee.

00:37:27.467 --> 00:37:30.100
Can we do this later?
Someone might hear.

00:37:36.085 --> 00:37:36.900
Then come here.

00:37:37.100 --> 00:37:38.260
No.

00:37:43.460 --> 00:37:44.620
All clear.

00:37:45.580 --> 00:37:49.060
Now spill it, Mr. Croissant.

00:37:56.492 --> 00:37:58.620
“Croissant” is a nickname
my mom gave me.

00:37:59.420 --> 00:38:00.580
My dad hates it.

00:38:02.571 --> 00:38:03.460
…Yeah,

00:38:04.620 --> 00:38:05.980
I get why.

00:38:07.020 --> 00:38:13.060
Imagine an MP named Croissant.

00:38:14.170 --> 00:38:16.020
Wouldn’t it be ridiculous?
Think about it.

00:38:16.550 --> 00:38:17.540
“Good evening, everyone.

00:38:17.610 --> 00:38:20.140
I’m MP Croissant
from the Wiwat Siam Party.”

00:38:21.407 --> 00:38:25.220
That’s why it’s a burner account,
my secret identity.

00:38:27.657 --> 00:38:29.740
I only use it to lurk and follow.

00:38:30.300 --> 00:38:31.900
I’m not doing anything behind your back,
by the way.

00:38:32.950 --> 00:38:34.220
I didn’t say you were.

00:38:35.340 --> 00:38:36.500
Jumpy much?

00:38:39.342 --> 00:38:42.700
I just want to know
what you talk about with the shippers.

00:38:44.660 --> 00:38:46.660
I blend in like any fan.

00:38:47.250 --> 00:38:51.820
Stir the hype a bit and ask
if they think the two are for real.

00:38:52.735 --> 00:38:53.820
And are they?

00:38:56.750 --> 00:38:58.060
You asking the shippers,

00:38:59.340 --> 00:39:00.460
or us?

00:39:07.514 --> 00:39:08.740
I’m asking you.

00:39:11.200 --> 00:39:12.100
Is this real?

00:39:15.028 --> 00:39:16.380
If it were a sure thing,

00:39:18.820 --> 00:39:20.260
it wouldn’t be a “ship,” would it?

00:39:26.550 --> 00:39:29.660
Then let’s stop being a ship.

00:39:37.340 --> 00:39:38.540
Let’s be the real deal.

00:39:39.380 --> 00:39:40.980
Ha,

00:39:41.500 --> 00:39:43.380
you’re smiling.

00:39:44.142 --> 00:39:48.460
- What, I can’t smile?
- You can.

00:39:50.860 --> 00:39:53.300
I just want to know
if we’re smiling about the same thing.

00:40:30.190 --> 00:40:32.220
Here’s your late-night congee.

00:40:32.371 --> 00:40:33.740
Nice.

00:40:34.260 --> 00:40:40.140
Sir, I’m so honored to have
your company on this all-nighter.

00:40:40.514 --> 00:40:42.820
Haven’t you already pulled three?

00:40:42.990 --> 00:40:49.340
And whose dad made me
sign those stacks of paperwork, huh?

00:40:52.110 --> 00:40:53.860
Been butting heads
with Dr. Chalong forever.

00:40:55.057 --> 00:40:57.500
And now I’m supposed
to rubber-stamp it? No way.

00:40:58.600 --> 00:40:59.940
So yeah, I’m pushing back.

00:41:00.830 --> 00:41:05.940
And tomorrow
I’m hitting Sun’s bull’s-eye.

00:41:06.400 --> 00:41:08.100
Watch what you say.

00:41:08.285 --> 00:41:10.220
Don’t act shy.

00:41:10.660 --> 00:41:13.380
We’re going in
to make gains on his turf.

00:41:13.690 --> 00:41:16.980
If that’s not going straight
for the bull’s-eye, what is?

00:41:17.514 --> 00:41:18.620
Suit yourself.

00:41:19.460 --> 00:41:22.660
Let’s eat, I’ll prepare it.

00:41:24.740 --> 00:41:25.740
Sit.

00:41:26.980 --> 00:41:28.660
Thank you, boss.

00:42:14.750 --> 00:42:18.740
Our Tele-Doctor program
has received a very positive response

00:42:19.360 --> 00:42:21.900
because we have worked
with full dedication.

00:42:22.100 --> 00:42:26.140
With the cooperation
of local medical staff,

00:42:26.500 --> 00:42:29.340
we have been able to work efficiently.

00:42:29.950 --> 00:42:31.780
Let’s invite the person behind it,

00:42:32.020 --> 00:42:34.460
so our friends in the press
don’t have to wait.

00:42:34.885 --> 00:42:36.740
Please welcome
Dr. Thanit Phonthongdee,

00:42:36.940 --> 00:42:39.460
Minister of Public Health.

00:42:43.390 --> 00:42:45.940
Cancel the event,
and take the doctor to rest first.

00:42:46.220 --> 00:42:48.580
No photos, please.

00:42:54.030 --> 00:42:55.860
I’ve been on it for twenty years.

00:42:58.300 --> 00:42:59.740
There’s never been a problem.

00:43:01.771 --> 00:43:03.300
You’re not addicted to it, are you?

00:43:05.828 --> 00:43:07.580
I told you,

00:43:08.650 --> 00:43:12.140
it’s a psych med, not a narcotic.

00:43:15.000 --> 00:43:17.140
It’s just not legal in Thailand yet.

00:43:20.114 --> 00:43:21.340
And where did you get it?

00:43:22.160 --> 00:43:23.580
I’ve got my pharmacist friend...

00:43:25.300 --> 00:43:26.620
to buy it for me.

00:43:27.857 --> 00:43:31.420
You need to stop. Today. Now.

00:43:33.280 --> 00:43:35.420
- I’ll be more careful, okay?
- No.

00:43:37.500 --> 00:43:40.020
Yffou crashed and burned
on camera today.

00:43:41.028 --> 00:43:43.140
Ying already covered for me.

00:43:43.870 --> 00:43:45.620
She said I was exhausted
from working too hard.

00:43:45.780 --> 00:43:46.940
It makes sense.

00:43:47.060 --> 00:43:48.940
You don’t think people will start digging?

00:43:50.260 --> 00:43:51.900
No one’s going to get suspicious?

00:43:53.570 --> 00:43:56.220
And Trirat is about to bring
a no-confidence motion against you.

00:43:56.620 --> 00:44:01.300
You’re handing them ammunition.

00:44:02.620 --> 00:44:05.260
If you don’t quit, you’re finished.

00:44:05.360 --> 00:44:06.980
Do you have any sympathy for me at all?

00:44:09.100 --> 00:44:13.180
If I didn’t have to swallow these rotten deals
and put up with selfish people,

00:44:13.940 --> 00:44:15.580
I wouldn’t be doing this.

00:44:16.100 --> 00:44:18.860
Then admit you can’t handle it.

00:44:24.190 --> 00:44:27.700
You’re not just
a provincial hospital doctor anymore.

00:44:28.660 --> 00:44:30.700
Build as big a team as you need.

00:44:32.650 --> 00:44:36.140
And if you don’t trust anyone, tell me.

00:44:43.800 --> 00:44:45.060
I’m sorry, Vee.

00:44:51.100 --> 00:44:52.460
Forget that for now.

00:44:56.371 --> 00:44:59.060
Bottom line: you have to stop, for good.

00:45:00.180 --> 00:45:01.380
- I told you I...
- Enough.

00:45:06.257 --> 00:45:07.500
We’ll talk later.

00:45:09.510 --> 00:45:10.980
You need to rest.

00:45:43.490 --> 00:45:44.700
Hi, Gale.

00:45:45.970 --> 00:45:47.500
How solid is the evidence?

00:45:49.930 --> 00:45:53.580
Okay, go ahead.
If you hit any snags, tell me.

00:45:57.340 --> 00:46:00.940
If you won’t take it from me,
at least listen to the doctor.

00:46:02.914 --> 00:46:04.100
You need to rehab.

00:46:12.871 --> 00:46:15.260
Last night, police received
a report of a drug party

00:46:15.380 --> 00:46:16.580
You need to watch this.

00:46:16.780 --> 00:46:17.860
at a luxury condo downtown.

00:46:18.180 --> 00:46:20.740
When officers arrived,
there was no gathering

00:46:20.980 --> 00:46:25.300
but the unit turned out to be the residence
of Dr. Thanit Phonthongdee,

00:46:25.490 --> 00:46:29.620
better known as Dr. Nong,
the Minister of Public Health.

00:46:29.885 --> 00:46:32.780
At first, it looked like
a politically motivated tip.

00:46:32.930 --> 00:46:35.300
But here’s what officers say they found.

00:46:35.471 --> 00:46:38.660
What you’re seeing here
is a stimulant drug,

00:46:38.780 --> 00:46:43.340
classified under Thai law
as a Category 2 controlled substance.

00:46:52.085 --> 00:46:53.420
We have to hold
a press conference today.

00:46:53.780 --> 00:46:56.140
If we don’t have an answer
within the hour,

00:46:57.500 --> 00:46:59.260
the Prime Minister’s Office will take over.

00:47:06.860 --> 00:47:08.020
What’s the move?

00:47:09.020 --> 00:47:10.820
We can’t let Jes take care of this.

00:47:35.660 --> 00:47:36.500
Doc,

00:47:40.260 --> 00:47:41.740
will you do whatever it takes?

00:47:46.940 --> 00:47:47.780
Ni,

00:47:49.900 --> 00:47:50.980
go get Jump.

00:48:02.280 --> 00:48:06.580
The drug shown in the reports...

00:48:08.550 --> 00:48:10.060
is a psychiatric stimulant.

00:48:11.780 --> 00:48:16.260
It helps with alertness and focus.

00:48:18.980 --> 00:48:22.420
However, it isn’t approved by the Thai FDA

00:48:23.630 --> 00:48:28.340
and is classified under Thai law
as a Category 2 controlled substance.

00:48:30.857 --> 00:48:32.980
I want to sincerely apologize
to the public.

00:48:36.700 --> 00:48:38.100
This is my responsibility.

00:48:43.428 --> 00:48:46.300
I failed to look after my nephew,
who lives with me,

00:48:47.820 --> 00:48:50.420
and he became involved
in something illegal.

00:48:50.828 --> 00:48:53.180
What is wrong can never be right.

00:48:53.780 --> 00:48:56.580
My nephew will go through
the legal process.

00:48:57.000 --> 00:48:59.380
To be clear, are you saying the drug
belonged to your nephew?

00:49:02.010 --> 00:49:02.940
Yes.

00:49:05.457 --> 00:49:07.620
We live together
in the same apartment.

00:49:07.857 --> 00:49:09.660
And you had no
prior knowledge of this?

00:49:09.870 --> 00:49:13.540
Right, how could you not know
if you live together?

00:49:15.160 --> 00:49:16.540
I didn’t know.

00:49:21.271 --> 00:49:22.980
I have Dr. Nong’s nephew
remanded for now.

00:49:23.520 --> 00:49:26.140
We’ll post bail later
when the timing’s right.

00:49:26.700 --> 00:49:30.180
And when this is wrapped up,
don’t forget to buy me some wine.

00:49:30.914 --> 00:49:31.660
Understood.

00:49:32.940 --> 00:49:34.140
That’s all for now.

00:49:49.400 --> 00:49:50.340
Hey, Boss.

00:49:51.660 --> 00:49:52.460
Hey,

00:49:56.314 --> 00:49:57.300
I’m fine.

00:50:02.700 --> 00:50:04.020
It’s the VIP holding.

00:50:06.578 --> 00:50:07.540
Decent bed

00:50:08.740 --> 00:50:10.220
and no one’s gonna touch me.

00:50:12.742 --> 00:50:15.780
No shanks, no ‘initiation.’

00:50:17.040 --> 00:50:19.620
I’ll walk out without a scratch.

00:50:23.220 --> 00:50:25.140
Can’t promise about pearling, though.

00:50:28.485 --> 00:50:29.940
I’m really sorry, Jump.

00:50:36.178 --> 00:50:37.540
This is on me.

00:50:44.740 --> 00:50:45.740
It’s alright.

00:50:51.170 --> 00:50:53.500
I’m more useful in here if it means

00:50:55.880 --> 00:50:57.820
you can be out there
getting things done.

00:51:02.342 --> 00:51:04.460
I’ll be out soon anyway.

00:51:05.942 --> 00:51:09.140
When you get out,

00:51:11.860 --> 00:51:13.940
you’ll have a record, Jump.
You know that, right?

00:51:15.171 --> 00:51:16.900
Worst case, I’m an ex-convict.

00:51:18.690 --> 00:51:20.460
But without you,

00:51:24.141 --> 00:51:25.980
I’m just a nobody.

00:51:33.670 --> 00:51:35.060
And “ex-con”

00:51:36.970 --> 00:51:38.380
sounds cooler
than “nobody,” doesn’t it?

00:51:41.171 --> 00:51:42.220
Believe me,

00:51:43.460 --> 00:51:44.980
you’re more than that.

00:51:55.860 --> 00:51:57.100
Damn it.

00:52:05.100 --> 00:52:11.660
Amid growing skepticism surrounding
Health Minister Dr. Thanit,

00:52:11.900 --> 00:52:18.380
an online petition urging his resignation
has gathered 64,512 signatures.

00:52:18.600 --> 00:52:22.180
Joining us now is Mr. Hari,
legal adviser to the Deputy Prime Minister.

00:52:22.380 --> 00:52:24.940
Mr. Hari, what’s your view?

00:53:02.720 --> 00:53:04.220
If you felt guilty about Jump,

00:53:05.500 --> 00:53:07.260
half of that’s on me.

00:53:10.714 --> 00:53:12.300
I’m a selfish bastard.

00:53:14.114 --> 00:53:15.060
That’s not true.

00:53:16.440 --> 00:53:17.900
For the Tele-Doctor project,

00:53:18.420 --> 00:53:20.060
who is the one who keeps
pushing back on Dr. Chalong?

00:53:20.540 --> 00:53:23.260
- Who leaned on the suppliers?
- And we still couldn’t beat them.

00:53:28.028 --> 00:53:29.460
They took it all.

00:53:30.540 --> 00:53:31.820
How much was left for the ministry?

00:53:32.530 --> 00:53:33.700
Go and take a look at

00:53:36.100 --> 00:53:37.340
how much is left?

00:53:39.580 --> 00:53:40.900
They’re all rotten to the core.

00:53:42.542 --> 00:53:43.380
Trust me,

00:53:44.020 --> 00:53:45.260
without you,

00:53:46.660 --> 00:53:48.300
it would’ve been a lot worse.

00:53:49.171 --> 00:53:50.540
Maybe we didn’t win,

00:53:51.090 --> 00:53:53.580
- but we didn’t lose either.
- Don’t talk like you know.

00:53:57.430 --> 00:53:59.140
I’m worse than you think.

00:54:00.714 --> 00:54:02.500
If you feel guilty about Jump,

00:54:05.170 --> 00:54:06.500
then go to rehab..

00:54:11.685 --> 00:54:13.260
It’s not just Jump.

00:54:20.260 --> 00:54:22.020
There’s worse.

00:54:24.200 --> 00:54:25.500
And if you knew,

00:54:28.540 --> 00:54:30.460
you could walk away right now.

00:54:46.428 --> 00:54:47.900
I was high,

00:54:55.628 --> 00:54:57.020
really high.

00:55:01.142 --> 00:55:02.860
So I chose Chief Tong,

00:55:07.370 --> 00:55:09.260
because I knew I couldn’t handle it.

00:55:11.000 --> 00:55:13.340
I was afraid if I chose my father…

00:55:18.050 --> 00:55:20.220
I’d end up getting my own father killed.

00:55:25.771 --> 00:55:28.380
How messed up do I have to be...

00:55:30.950 --> 00:55:32.580
to do that?

00:55:34.500 --> 00:55:35.460
I’m a piece of shit,

00:55:37.114 --> 00:55:39.020
right? Am I?

00:55:41.057 --> 00:55:42.460
Just stay away from me.

00:55:43.050 --> 00:55:44.340
Hey, easy.

00:55:48.380 --> 00:55:49.900
What’s done is done.

00:55:53.800 --> 00:55:54.900
It’s okay.

00:56:05.035 --> 00:56:06.060
I’m here.

00:56:28.240 --> 00:56:29.860
And… thanks for telling me everything.

00:56:34.371 --> 00:56:38.020
Tee, you say you’ve brought new evidence.
What is it exactly?

00:56:38.160 --> 00:56:41.820
It’s the original operative note from that day.
It’s Dr. Nong’s own surgical log.

00:56:42.020 --> 00:56:46.860
If the evidence used in the case proves false,

00:56:47.130 --> 00:56:51.140
we can reopen the case.

00:56:51.460 --> 00:56:55.740
The note says he asked for five minutes
before entering the operating room.

00:56:56.100 --> 00:56:59.380
And when he came back,
he appeared disoriented,

00:56:59.900 --> 00:57:04.180
which the attending nurse says contributed to a delay in treatment.

00:57:04.342 --> 00:57:05.700
That’s significant,

00:57:05.980 --> 00:57:09.620
those symptoms can be consistent
with drug use.

00:57:09.890 --> 00:57:14.660
And Dr. Nong has also said the drugs
were obtained by his nephew.

00:57:14.828 --> 00:57:18.380
I’m here today to ask the public
to watch closely

00:57:18.610 --> 00:57:23.700
for any political interference in this case.

00:57:23.971 --> 00:57:27.620
This isn’t just about grudges or personal failings.

00:57:27.780 --> 00:57:30.300
It’s a question of political ethics,

00:57:30.450 --> 00:57:35.740
and it could weigh heavily on
the upcoming no-confidence debate.